title: Police looking into deaths of five people on Titanic submersible
description: Canadian police are looking into the deaths of five people killed in the implosion of the Titan submersible.

title: Ex-Premier League striker dies aged 45
description: Tributes have been paid to former Coventry and Wolves striker Cedric Roussel who has died at the age of 45.

title: How does Wagner's strength measure up to the Russian military?
description: The boss of the Wagner mercenary group appears to fancy his chances when it comes to the march on Moscow - something Russian leader Vladimir Putin has called "armed mutiny".

title: Russia civil unrest triggered by Wagner mercenary mutiny offers hope to Ukrainians
description: After a year and a half of unrelenting gloom, finally news for Ukrainians to celebrate.

title: Dangerous Wagner mercenary boss was disaster waiting to happen for Putin
description: Wagner boss Yevgeny Prigozhin is now a problem entirely of the Kremlin's making.

title: Hot dog seller to mercenary boss: Who is Wagner Group leader Prigozhin?
description: From flea market hot dog seller to the head of a mercenary group behind a mutiny against the Russian military, Yevgeny Prigozhin's rise has been far from ordinary.

title: Vladimir Putin calls Wagner rebellion 'armed mutiny' and 'stab in the back'
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has accused the leader of the Wagner mercenary group of treason and leading an "armed mutiny".

title: US Coast Guard to lead Titan sub investigation following five-day search 'costing millions'
description: The US Coast Guard will lead the investigation into the implosion of the Titan submersible which killed five people.

title: Prigozhin's rebellion could trigger Putin's most serious domestic crisis
description: An extraordinary rebellion by the head of Russia's Wagner mercenary group could trigger the gravest domestic crisis for Vladimir Putin since his full-scale invasion of Ukraine.

title: 'No direct evidence' COVID started in Wuhan lab - US intelligence
description: A US intelligence report has found no direct evidence that COVID started in China's Wuhan Institute of Virology.
